./.title: Introduction
./.body:
Generate projects or files from template.
Features

Various ways to input value for user-defined variable
Include repetitive content with include variable
Time stamp with customizable format
Prehook, posthook scripts
Built in system-wide template management system

installation.html.title: Installation
installation.html.body:
Installation

summon/bin
bin file
flint swift system https://github.com/flintbox/Flint 0.1.8
Execute
summon/bin flint version

Homebrew
brew install flintbox/Flint/flint

Mint
mint install flintbox/Flint

Make
Install
git clone https://github.com/flintbox/Flint
cd Flint
make

Uninstall
make uninstall

create-template.html.title: Create template
create-template.html.body:
Create template

Template directory structure
Template
└╴template.json
└╴template
  └╴[PROJECT FILES]
└╴include
  └╴[FILES USED FOR INCLUDE VARIABLES]
└╴prehooks
  └╴[PREHOOK SCRIPTS]
└╴posthooks
  └╴[POSTHOOK SCRIPTS]

template-json.html.title: template.json
template-json.html.body:
template.json

Template manifest file. YAML is also supported.
{
  "description": "Template description",
  "variables": [
    {
      "name": "Author"
    },
    {
      "name": "MODULE_NAME",
      "displayName": "Module Name (Module name for the package.)",
      "defaultValue": "CLI"
    }
  ],
  "prehooks": [
    "script1.sh",
    "script2.sh",
    "script3.sh"
  ],
  "posthooks": [
    "script4.sh",
    "script5.sh"
  ]
}

description
Template description. This field is optional.
variables
Variable used in template. Each item has name and optional displayName, defaultValue. When displayName exists, it is used instead of name on CLI. This field is optional.
prehooks
Prehook scripts. These scripts will be executed in sequence before the variables are processed. Scripts can use FLINT_OUTPUT_PATH and FLINT_+EACH_VARIABLE_NAME (Whitespaces replaced with underscores.) environment variable. This field is optional.
posthooks
Posthook scripts. These scripts will be executed in sequence after the variables are processed. Scripts can use FLINT_OUTPUT_PATH and FLINT_+EACH_VARIABLE_NAME (Whitespaces replaced with underscores.) environment variable. This field is optional.

variable.html.title: Variable
variable.html.body:
Variable

Name of file and folder or content of file can have variables.
Available variable formats

__VARIABLE_NAME__
___VARIABLE_NAME___
--VARIABLE_NAME--
{{VARIABLE_NAME}}

predefined-variable.html.title: Predefined variable
predefined-variable.html.body:
Predefined variable

Beside custom variables, several predefined variables are also available.
File attribute
File name
Following variables are processed into final output file name.
__FILE:NAME__
___FILE:NAME___
--FILE:NAME--
{{FILE:NAME}}
Include file variable
You can include other files under include/ on template files or directory names with following variables.
__INCLUDE:PATH TO FILE__
___INCLUDE:PATH TO FILE___
--INCLUDE:PATH TO FILE--
{{INCLUDE:PATH TO FILE}}
For example, read file include/license/MIT and replace variable with the content.
{{INCLUDE:license/MIT}}
Date variable
Date variable has following form and processed with Swift DateFormatter.
__DATE:LOCALE|DATE FORMAT__
___DATE:LOCALE|DATE FORMAT___
--DATE:LOCALE|DATE FORMAT--
{{DATE:LOCALE|DATE FORMAT}}
LOCALE is optional locale identifier.
DATE FORMAT can be one of the following values.



Type
Description




YEAR
Date format yyyy


YEAR-SHORT
Date format yy


MONTH
Date format MM


MONTH-SHORT
Date format M


DAY
Date format dd


DAY-SHORT
Date format d


SHORT
System short date style


MEDIUM
System medium date style


LONG
System long date style


FULL
System full date style


Any String Value
Any date format needed



Examples,
{{DATE:YEAR}} // 2018
{{DATE:ko_KR|FULL}} // 2018년 6월 20일 수요일
--DATE:yyyy M dd-- // 2018 6 20

environment-variable.html.title: Environment variable
environment-variable.html.body:
Environment variable

Template home
FLINT_TEMPLATE_HOME

Set path for template home.
Preset value
FLINT_+VARIABLE_NAME (Whitespaces replaced with underscores.)
You can preset value for template variable on environment variables. For example, if there is a variable named Owner Name and you set environment variables as following
FLINT_Owner_Name=Jason Nam

Now, value for Owner Name will be automatically collected and skipped on interactive spark command. If the same value presented on input file, value on file will override environment variable.

template-add.html.title: Add
template-add.html.body:
Add

Copy template to template home path.
Command
flint template add  [] [--force | -f] [--verbose | -v]

or
flint t a  [] [--force | -f] [--verbose | -v]

Argument

Path to template.
[]
Template name. This is sub path relative to template home. If not present, the value will be the last path component of path to template.
Option
[--force | -f]
Override existing template under template home.
[--verbose | -v]
Output more information.

template-clone.html.title: Clone
template-clone.html.body:
Clone

Clone template repository to template home path.
Command
flint template clone  [] [--branch | -b ] [--force | -f] [--verbose | -v]

or
flint t c  [] [--branch | -b ] [--force | -f] [--verbose | -v]

Argument

Repository URL to clone.
[]
Template name. This is sub path relative to template home. If not present, the value will be the name from repository URL.
Option
[--branch | -b ]
Branch to clone.
[--force | -f]
Override existing template under template home.
[--verbose | -v]
Output more information.

template-list.html.title: List
template-list.html.body:
List

List available templates under template home.
Command
flint template list [--verbose | -v]

or
flint t l [--verbose | -v]

Option
[--verbose | -v]
Output more information.

template-remove.html.title: Remove
template-remove.html.body:
Remove

Remove templates under template home.
Command
flint template remove ... [--verbose | -v]

or
flint t r ... [--verbose | -v]

Argument
...
Templates to remove from template home.
Option
[--verbose | -v]
Output more information.

spark.html.title: Spark
spark.html.body:
Spark

Generate project from template.
Command
flint spark [] [--template | -t ] [--output | -o ] [--input | -i ] [--force | -f] [--verbose | -v]

or
flint s [] [--template | -t ] [--output | -o ] [--input | -i ] [--force | -f] [--verbose | -v]

Argument
[]
Template from template home to use.
Option
[--template | -t ]
Path for template to use. If template name argument is presented, this value will be ignored.
[--output | -o ]
Path to write generated project. If not presented, current path for the process will be used.
[--input | -i ]
Variable input file path.
[--force | -f]
Override output path.
[--verbose | -v]
Output more information.

input.html.title: Input
input.html.body:
Input

Generate variable input file from template.
Command
flint input [] [--template | -t ] [--output | -o ] [--yaml | -y] [--force | -f] [--verbose | -v]

or
flint i [] [--template | -t ] [--output | -o ] [--yaml | -y] [--force | -f] [--verbose | -v]

Argument
[]
Template from template home to use.
Option
[--template | -t ]
Path for template to use. If template name argument is presented, this value will be ignored.
[--output | -o ]
Path to write generated file. If not presented, current path for the process will be used.
[--yaml | -y]
Use YAML format. If not presented, JSON format will be used.
[--force | -f]
Override output path.
[--verbose | -v]
Output more information.
